ny unused fields and whether Checkstyle might allow visibility modifier issues. There are existing private static inner fields that aren't marked final. I noticed that while using private final fields, JOL uses reflection without compile warnings. I also want to ensure existing classes and methods comply with Java conventions. The problem arises with the developer’s warning against using dynamic-class-loading patterns for standard reflection, which seems unavoidable here. I'll need to inspect the reports and consider potential native calls.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring plugin settings and JVM behavior**\\n\\nThis is part of the plugin, and I need to confirm if \\\"direct reflection\\\" is avoided—okay. There's a concern that `System.setProperty(\\\"jdk.attach.allowAttachSelf\\\",\\\"true\\\")` may not apply in JDK9+ because it reads saved properties at VM startup. I think the property can be set at runtime, but it seems HotSpot checks saved properties instead. I wonder if altering the test JVM arguments in build.gradle would impact all tests, especially regarding native tests. I might need to consider using a public API to launch a separate JVM with `-javaagent:jol-core.jar`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering alternatives for memory layout**\\n\\nI'm thinking of alternatives here, and it seems I could use `ClassLayout.toPrintable` instead of `VMSupport.sizeOf`. It feels like this could be enough to achieve what I need without relying on the latter. I wonder if this approach simplifies things and minimizes potential complications. Using `ClassLayout.toPrintable` might provide the clarity I'm looking for in understanding memory layout, which sounds like a more straightforward option. It's worth exploring further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring dynamic attach behavior**\\n\\nSo, I’ve determined that TRY_DYNAMIC_ATTACH will be false, meaning it won't make an attempt again and will give a fallback size. If toPrintable succeeds in attaching, VMSupport.sizeOf may use instrumentation. The user mentioned “remaining uncovered dynamic-access call sites.” Our test reaches tryDynamicAttach unless static TRY false. I’m wondering if a JVM system property, like `jol.skipDynamicAttach`, is set in the test harness—if true, then dynamic attach won't happen. I should search for that!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_aTB1nTON4KrA0Xvv91FBpf0b|fc_009820b8aefa0f84016a2435c152208196b5d1173f31b749f6", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"jol.skipDynamicAttach|allowAttachSelf|native-image.properties|runtimeArgs|testRuntimeArgs|graalvmNative|nativeTest\" -n tests/src/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.4 build.gradle gradle.properties settings.gradle 2>/dev/null", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1020, "output": 722, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36046, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780757935612, "responseId": "resp_009820b8aefa0f84016a2435b010fc8196b92128b2aba3e5fa"}}
